CRACKER EXTERMINATOR


                     The CRACKER Exterminator-Virus is a boot virus, which
                     copies   itself  always  to  the  same memory-address
                     $7EA00.  It  changes  the  CoolCapture-Vector to stay
                      resident in memory.


                     If  the virus-copy-value reaches 4 the virus executes
                     a Headstep-Routine. This routine can even damage your
                     drives if you`re unlucky, so BE CAREFUL.


                     In the top of the Bootblock you can read:

                     "The CRACKER Exterminator"

                     In the end there is a crypted text, decrypted you can
                     read:

                     "Hi hacker! your Amiga is infected with a new"
                     "generation of virus called:"
                     "The CRACKER Exterminator! made by A:C:C:W"
                     "[Anti-Cracker-Club-West] have fun you fucking"
                     "cracker !"

                     This bootvirus does not need the trackdisk.device. In
                     the  bootblock you can read the following ASCII text:
                     "Cascade V2.1CCount".

                  .  By  using  Kickstart  2.0 and later versions you will
                     probably get a guru.

                  .  By  using  Kickstart 1.3  your  mousepointer  will be
                     transformed into a penis.

@Endnode


